x4freetext: Details of the measurement instruments and processing
Gas target (0.2 MPa) contained in a cylindrical
stainless steel cell (0.5 mm thick, 3 cm long) with a
Mo foil entrance window (5 um thick) and Au plate
detector in a 25.4 cm (diam) x 25.4 cm (long) NaI(Tl)
annular detector in an anti-coincidence mode to
5 cm (diam) x 1.27 cm (long) NE213 for neutron
- attenuation of incident neutrons and emitted gammas,
and multiple scattering of neutrons by a code MNSCAT
- secondary gamma-ray production due to Compton
- low energy neutrons (for En=10 MeV and 13 MeV). The
low energy neutron contribution at En=13 MeV is
performed with the gamma production cross sections
measured at ORNL or those measured at 7.8 MeV in
(3% for Eg<2 MeV, 8% for Eg=11 MeV)
